HB 405 Engrossed 2026 Regular Session Egan
Abstract: Provides for the name change of the national organization that certifies
acupuncturists.
Present law provides that to be licensed as an acupuncturist one must hold active status with
the National Certification Commission for Acupuncture and Oriental Medicine and pass the
certification examination.
Proposed law changes the organization's name change from the National Certification
Commission for Acupuncture and Oriental Medicine to the National Certification Board for
Acupuncture and Herbal Medicine.
(Amends R.S. 37:1358)
